
[1]batenists

   BAT'ENITES, BAT'ENISTS, or BATE'NIANS, n. A sect of apostates from
   Mohammedism, who professed the abominable practices of the Ismaelians
   and Kirmatians. The word signified esoteric,or persons of inward light.
   [See Assassins.]

